# digiquant-atlas — Cursor Rules

## What This Project Is
Daily market intelligence repo using a **9-phase** AI-orchestrated pipeline. Skills are `skills/<slug>/SKILL.md`. **DB-first**: Supabase + JSON canonical; markdown derived for display.

## Core Architecture
- `skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md` — master pipeline (read this first for context)
- `config/watchlist.md` + `config/preferences.md` — user configuration
- No repo-local cache for canonical state — Supabase only. `data/agent-cache/` is legacy/migration/fetch-temp only (see `data/README.md`).
- `python3 scripts/run_db_first.py` — post-publish metrics + validate entry

## Web Fetch Protocol
When following any URL to read an article, news page, speech, or filing:
```bash
defuddle parse <url> --md   # strips nav/ads before the LLM reads
```
Do NOT use defuddle for `.md` files, `.json` endpoints, or Supabase/API URLs.

## Token Mode Protocol
- **Caveman ON** for: phase announcements, triage, checkpoints, inter-phase reasoning
- **Normal mode** for: any content going to Supabase (narratives, rationale, recommendations)
- Toggle: say `normal mode` before authoring DB content, `caveman mode` after publishing

## Research Library
```bash
python3 scripts/fetch_research_library.py             # list Supabase research index
python3 scripts/fetch_research_library.py --ticker X  # filter by ticker
python3 scripts/publish_research.py \
  --key research/deep-dives/TICKER-DATE \
  --title "Title" --type deep-dive --content -        # publish new note
```
Static doctrine papers: `docs/research/papers/` (7 files, git-tracked, read-only).

## Skill File Rules
When editing `skills/<slug>/SKILL.md` files:
- YAML frontmatter `name:` and `description:` are sacred — do NOT rename without updating `docs/agentic/SKILLS-CATALOG.md`
- Include defuddle web fetch note in any skill that browses the web
- Output paths use `{{DATE}}` placeholder — never hardcode dates
- Keep numbered Steps format: `### 1. Step Name` throughout

## Script Rules
- All scripts: `#!/bin/bash` + `set -e` at top
- macOS sed: use `sed -i ""` NOT `sed -i` (critical — macOS incompatibility otherwise)
- All paths are relative to repo root

## Output Rules
- DB-first: Supabase is canonical; publish via `publish_document.py --payload -`
- Do not treat `data/agent-cache/` as task output — migration/fetch tooling only (`data/README.md`)

## Markdown Standards
- Headings: `#` then `##` then `###` — never skip levels
- Tables: always include `|---|---|` separator row
- Templates use `{{PLACEHOLDER}}` syntax for runtime substitution

## Forbidden Actions
- Do NOT modify `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` without understanding CI/CD
- Do NOT change skill frontmatter `name:` fields without cascading updates
- Do NOT hand-edit Supabase rows directly — use `publish_document.py` / `materialize_snapshot.py`

## Documentation Index
- `CLAUDE.md` — Claude Code reference
- `AGENTS.md` — Cross-platform agent reference
- `docs/agentic/` — Full documentation suite
- `docs/agentic/ARCHITECTURE.md` — System design
- `docs/agentic/SKILLS-CATALOG.md` — All skills indexed
